RENDER extension implementation for python-xlib
-----------------------------------------------

This is a work-in-progress; the interface can and will change.

To test this, copy render.py to the ext/ directory under Xlib.
You also need to make some changes to other files:
- Add to __extensions__ in Xlib.ext.__init__:
    ('RENDER', 'render'),
- Add to Xlib.display, at the top:
    import ext.render
- Add to _resource_baseclasses in Xlib.display:
    'picture': ext.render.Picture,
    'glyphset': ext.render.GlyphSet,
- Add to 'resource' entry of _resource_hierarchy in Xlib.display:
    'picture',
    'glyphset',
- Add to Xlib.protocol.rq, after the other resources:
    class Picture(Resource):
        cast_function = '__picture__'
        class_name = 'picture'

    class GlyphSet(Resource):
        cast_function = '__glyphset__'
        class_name = 'glyphset'
- Add support for multiple fields to LengthOf in Xlib.protocol.rq:
  - Not strictly necessary, since it is only used in requests
  - Implementation can be found at: http://sourceforge.net/mailarchive/forum.php?thread_name=20120703192708.1e620fe7%40bhuda.mired.org&forum_name=python-xlib-users

I bet you'd have wanted a diff instead! (Maybe later)

